KW  - Interest rate swaps
KW  - Agency cost
KW  - Empirical study
AB  - This paper tests a model based on Wall's (Wall, L., 1989. Journal of Banking and Finance 13, 261–270) hypothesis of agency cost reduction using interest rate swaps. We find a significant positive relationship between the risk of the firm and the reduction of agency costs measured by the continuously compounded excess return (CAR) of the firm. Our findings are consistent with Wall’s hypothesis and other theories of swap transactions and in explaining the existence and growth of the swap market.
